Thanks for the PR. Making `GetPixels` public is reasonable — it's the only `WriteableBitmap` extension in this class that's still internal, and the use case (custom canvas implementations) is legitimate.

Before merging, would you be able to add XML documentation to the method? Since it returns a raw `IntPtr`, it would help consumers to know what the pointer refers to and when it's valid. Something like:

```csharp
/// <summary>
/// Gets a pointer to the pixel buffer of the <see cref="WriteableBitmap"/>.
/// </summary>
/// <param name="bitmap">The bitmap to get the pixels from.</param>
/// <returns>A pointer to the pixel buffer.</returns>
public static IntPtr GetPixels(this WriteableBitmap bitmap) =>
    bitmap.PixelBuffer.GetByteBuffer();
```

Also, the PR checklist mentions no tests — could you confirm whether the existing `SKXamlCanvas` tests cover this code path, or if a new test is needed?
